# Part 6 (15 minutes): Mini Project

Let's improve your patient registration program.

```python
print("====== Blood Reports App ======")

name = input("Enter Name: ").strip()

age = int(input("Enter Age: "))

gender = input("Enter Gender: ").strip()

blood_group = input("Enter Blood Group: ").strip()

hemoglobin = float(input("Enter Hemoglobin: "))

hba1c = float(input("Enter HbA1c: "))

vitamin_d = float(input("Enter Vitamin D: "))

print()

print("========== Patient Details ==========")

print("Name:", name)
print("Age:", age)
print("Gender:", gender)
print("Blood Group:", blood_group)
print("Hemoglobin:", hemoglobin)
print("HbA1c:", hba1c)
print("Vitamin D:", vitamin_d)

print("=====================================")
```

Notice how we now use:

* `int()` for age
* `float()` for blood values
* `.strip()` for text

This is much closer to how a real application works.

